<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="387" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Remarks</emphasis>
. In the key by zur Strassen (2003) this species runs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1990" box="[929,1057,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramadei">
<emphasis box="[929,1057,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. ramadei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1345,1398,259,285]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Italy</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Alavi &amp; Minaei, 2022" authorityName="Alavi &amp; Minaei" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitkini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. pitkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[231,295,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[231,295,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1990" box="[351,479,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramadei">
<emphasis box="[351,479,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. ramadei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unique among the known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[943,1092,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[943,1092,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Odontothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having antennal segment II with a tooth distally on the inner margin. These species are also similar in lacking teeth on the fore tarsi, having one small tooth at the fore tibia apex, and fore wing banded particularly in males. The females of these two species are not distinguishable, but the male of the new species is different from the male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1990" box="[1044,1170,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramadei">
<emphasis box="[1044,1170,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. ramadei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking canaliculi, in lacking a sub-apically directed strong tooth on the parameres (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bournier, A." box="[897,1063,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" pagination="199 - 206" refId="ref8170" refString="Bournier, A. (1990) Contributions la connaissance du genre Odontothrips Amyot et Serville (Thys. Thripidae). Bulletin de la Societ entomologiqe de France, 95, 199 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1990.17655" type="journal article" year="1990">Bournier 1990</bibRefCitation>
, p. 201, 
<figureCitation box="[1159,1240,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1179,1203]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,846,1153]" captionTargetId="figure-365@2.[151,1435,846,1153]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Odontothrips species. (1–3) Fore tarsus and apex of fore tibia, female: (1) O. meliloti, (2) O. moritzi, (3) O. confusus. (4–5) Abdominal tergites XI–X and genitalia, male: (4) O. meliloti, (5) O. confusus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450821/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
), and in having a series of dorsal fine ridges on the parameres medially (
<figureCitation box="[758,841,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–33" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,183,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[173,1414,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–33. Odontothrips pitkini sp. n. Female 18–29: (18) body, (19) antennal segments I–VIII, (20) antennal segments VI–VIII, (21–22) antennal segments I–III, (23–25) fore tarsus and apex of fore tibia (25 lateral views), (26) head &amp; pronotum, (27) meso- &amp; metanotum, (28) abdominal tergites VIII–X, (29) fore wing. Male 30–33: (30) body, (31) fore wing, (32) abdominal sternites IV– VII, (33) abdominal tergites XI–X and genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450827" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450827/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Alavi &amp; Minaei, 2022" authorityName="Alavi &amp; Minaei" authorityYear="2022" box="[1000,1105,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitkini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1000,1105,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. pitkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1111,1174,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1111,1174,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Alavi &amp; Minaei, 2022" authorityName="Alavi &amp; Minaei" authorityYear="2022" box="[213,300,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Odontothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bezii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[213,300,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. bezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[307,370,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[307,370,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by presence of a tooth on antennal segment II as well as the fore wings.
</paragraph>
